<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/705> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #705" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.26.12-13, and 40.8; Diod. 16.69.1, under 347; Cic. Sen. 60; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -Val]erius M. f. M. n. Corvus); Val. Max. 8.12.1;{130} 8.15.5; Plin. NH 7.157; Chr. 354 (Lenas IIII et Corvino); Fast. Hyd. (Corvino et Lenate III), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; on Popillius, Zosim. Hist. Nov. 2.4.1. See Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f. In this year the Antiates colonized Satricum and Rome made a treaty with Carthage (Liv. 7.27.3; cf. Polyb. 3.24; Diod. 16.69.1; Oros. 3.7.1). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 49, no. 49, on Popillius, Lübker, no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/704> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #704" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Valerius, see Act. Tr. on 335, and 349, note 4; and for that of Popillius, ib. on 350. Zosimus notes this as Popillius' fourth consulship." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/689> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #689" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.23.1; Diod. 16.56.1; Act. Tr.; Chr. 354 (Lenas III et Scipione); Fast. Hyd. (Scipione et Lenate II); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f. Scipio was kept from command by illness, while Popillius celebrated a triumph for a success over the Gauls (Liv. 7.23-24, and 25.1; and 25.1; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 540; App. Celt. 2). On Popillius, see Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/688> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #688" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Popilius, see Act. Tr. on 350. Scipio has the praenomen {Gr} in Diod." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/666> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #666" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Listed instead of Quinctius in some annals (Liv. 7.18.10), but not in Fast. Cap. See Lübker no. 4; Degrassi 405." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/664> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #664" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Fabius' name, see Act. Tr.; on that of Quinctius, Fast. Cap. on 361; and on that of Popillius, Act. Tr. on 350." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/658> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #658" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.17.1, both iterum; Diod. 16.32.1; Chr. 354 (Ambusto II et Lenas II), so also Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; see Degrassi 105, 402f. Fabius fought against Falerii and Tarquinii, Popillius against Tibur (Liv. 7.17.2-5; cf. Diod. 16.36.4; Frontin. Str. 2.4.18). On Popillius, see Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/657> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #657" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "For the name and filiation of Fabius, see Act. Tr. on 360 and 354; on that of Popillius, see Act. Tr. 350. Diod. has {Gr} for Popillius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/655> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #655" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Convicted Licinius Stolo of breaking his own law regarding possession of public land (Liv. 7.16.9; Val. Max. 8.6.3; cf. Dion. Hal. 14.12). See Lübker, no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/654> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #654" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Popillius' office is not named. In RE, the first edition, it is assumed that he was a Praetor, but Aediles levied fines for this offense (Liv. 10.13.14, 23.13, and 47.4; Mommsen, Str. 2.492ff.). The Curule Aediles of this year could be plebeians (Liv. 7.1.6), but Seidel (FA 9f.) thinks he was an Aedile of the Plebs. For the first plebeian Praetor, see 336, Praetors." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/645> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #645" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Brut. 56." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/644> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #644" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.12.1; Diod. 16.15.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Laenas; M.'s name entire); Fast. Hyd. (Lenate); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 105, 402f. Popillius quelled a popular sedition (Cic. Brut. 56; cf. Liv. 7.12.1-3). On Popillius, see Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/643> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #643" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Popillius, see Act. Tr. on 350; Degrassi 68f., 540. Livy has the nomen Pompilius and Cassiod. Papirius. The text in Diod. is {Gr}. In Chr. 354 the Consuls of 357 have been substituted by mistake." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/615> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #615" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In office when ludi scaenici were instituted (Fest. 436 L; cf. Liv. 7.2; Val. Max. 2.4.4). See Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10188> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10188" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Galleis. MRR I.127-8, Itgenshorst p. 264, Rich no. 62." .
